      "widgets_values": [
        "YOUR TASK:\nA 5-panel manga page, staggered layout. Style: Classic 90s aesthetic, delicate linework, heavy use of dot-pattern screentones for mood. Character: A tall man in a tattered trench coat with messy blonde hair.\n\nPanel 1 (Top Left): Close-up of his hand holding a cracked pocket watch. The time reads 11:59.\n\nPanel 2 (Top Right): He looks up at a clock tower in a snowy town square. Soft, melancholic expression.\n\nPanel 3 (Center): Large panel. He drops to his knees as the clock hits midnight. Snowflakes resting on his hair and shoulders. Text: \"Forgive me.\"\n\nPanel 4 (Bottom Left): Close-up of his face, a single tear frozen on his cheek. Teeth Grit.\n\nPanel 5 (Bottom Right): Wide shot from behind. He is a small silhouette in a vast, white field of snow. Text: \"The promise is broken.\""
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        -2240,
        -260
      ],
      "size": [
        500,
        1060
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 6,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 📌 ComfyUI Workflow Notes\n**Author:** Sharvin Suntoobacus  \n**YouTube Channel:** [CodeCraftersCorner](https://bit.ly/4b0o8dQ)  \n**Patreon:** [Support on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/codecrafterscorner)\n\n---\n\n### ℹ️ About This Workflow\nThis workflow is designed to leverage the **ERNIE-Image-Turbo** model for high-speed, consistent multi-panel manga generation and storyboarding. It allows users to maintain character and style consistency across sequential panels by using precise camera and action prompting. The workflow is optimised for 8-step inference, making it suitable for rapid narrative prototyping and high-fidelity text-to-image creation.\n\n### 🎥 Tutorial / Guide\n[Watch on YouTube](https://youtu.be/gzvh-zYx7Oo)  \n\n\n### 📥 Model Links (for Local Users)\nDownload the following models from the [Project Page](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ERNIE-Image):\n\n**diffusion_models**\n* [ernie-image-turbo.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ERNIE-Image/blob/main/diffusion_models/ernie-image-turbo.safetensors)\n\n**text_encoders**\n* [ministral-3-3b.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ERNIE-Image/blob/main/text_encoders/ministral-3-3b.safetensors)\n\n**vae**\n* [flux2-vae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/ERNIE-Image/blob/main/vae/flux2-vae.safetensors)\n\n### 📂 Model Storage Location\nPlace the downloaded files into the following directories within your ComfyUI installation:\n\n📂 **ComfyUI/**\n\n├── 📂 **models/**\n\n│   ├── 📂 **diffusion_models/**\n\n│   │   └── ernie-image-turbo.safetensors\n\n\n│   ├── 📂 **text_encoders/**\n\n│   │   └── ministral-3-3b.safetensors\n\n\n│   └── 📂 **vae/**\n\n│       └── flux2-vae.safetensors\n\n\n### 💡 Notes\n* **Resolution:** For optimal character proportions in multi-panel layouts, a \"tall\" orientation is recommended over a square 1024x1024 aspect ratio to prevent character compression/deformation.\n* **Consistency:** When regenerating specific panels, adjust the seed by +/- 1 to maintain character likeness while fixing minor generation errors.\n* **Grayscale Output:** If a traditional manga aesthetic is required, ensure the **ComfyUI-Ming-nodes** (or any saturation node) is installed to convert the output to grayscale.\n* **Hardware:** This workflow has been verified to run on 12GB VRAM.\n* **Workflow Download:** Get the JSON file here: [GitHub Archive](https://github.com/SharCodin/YouTube-Video-Archive/tree/main-branch/2026/Ernie)\n\n**Credit:** Please credit Sharvin Suntoobacus and share YouTube Channel Code Crafters Corner when sharing this workflow.  \n**Support:** Your support on Patreon helps me continue creating these guides!  \n\n🙏 **Thank you for your support!**"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
